helpdesk_ticket.description:
Greetings to you, 
 
 I hope this email reaches you in good health. First, I would like to introduce myself. My name is Cassidy Fejey, a British and also a staff member of an offshore bank (Standard Chartered Bank) London office. I'm the Head of Client Asset Management. I am pleased to pass you on to a very urgent and profitable business proposal which I believe will benefit both of us once completed. Please, I want you to take this proposal as a very important and genuine business transaction. I have contacted you after careful consideration that you are fit to handle this transaction which I will explain below. 
 
 The sum of €19,500,000.00 Euros (Nineteen Million, Five Hundred Thousand Euros) is not floating in my bank as all efforts to meet our client's relatives who filed the money have hit the rocks. helpdesk_ticket.description:
I had ordered a product on 20 November 2025 with order id -
650402234853142528. But in this i received totally wrong product with
different company and that too with open seal product box. So due to this i
filed return request for the same. On 26 november 2025 return order was
picked up successfully. But till now also my refund is not processed.
Firstly the wrong product was delivered and then the refund is being
delayed by saying that the refund will take more days and after the product
reach to them. It is already more than 5 days from pickup but my refund is
not processed yet. Wrong product delivered and then delaying refund and due
to this causing unnecessary inconvenience to me as refund should be
provided once the delivery agent verifies and after pickup as most other
online pharmacy and Ecommerce company does. This type of service was not
expected from pharmEasy. Order id - 650402234853142528 Transaction id -
T2511201235324232953202

I had multiple times raised this complaint to customer service with ticket
id - 22231676, 22233225, 22240350.
I also raised complaint on National consumer helpline also with grievance
id - 8256261.
But still no solution till now. Please look into this.

Thank you

--

helpdesk_ticket.description:
Dear Sir,

I had placed a lab test order for two patients, Rekha Pathak and Pranay
Pathak and availed the coupon benefit accordingly. The sample of Rekha
Pathak was successfully taken and that of Pranay Pathak could not be taken
as the technician impersonating to be Pradeep Gameti to whom the job was
assigned did not know the proper system and process to carry out the task.
Despite my protest with your customer care team the refund was initiated
withdrawing all the coupon benefits, which makes the tests very costly for
me for no fault of mine, while I requested to rebook the partly executed
order at no extra payment. The lab test is urgent. So get it done tomorrow
morning between 8 a.m. and 9 a.m. As a matter of your committed policy you
need not even charge for it, as the order couldn't be executed in time and
caused a great inconvenience to me. But what I'm requiring is to rebook the
unexecuted part with the amount purported to be the refund without any
additional payment.

Warm Regards,

Rajiv Pathak

--

The sample of Rekha Pathak was successfully taken and that of Pranay Pathak could not be taken as the technician impersonating to be Pradeep Gameti to whom the job was assigned did not know the proper system and process to carry out the task. Despite my protest with your customer care team the refund was initiated withdrawing all the coupon benefits, which makes the tests very costly for me for no fault of mine, while I requested to rebook the partly executed order at no extra payment. The lab test is urgent. So get it done tomorrow morning between 8 a.m. and 9 a.m. As a matter of your committed policy you need not even charge for it, as the order couldn't be executed in time and caused a great inconvenience to me. But what I'm requiring is to rebook the unexecuted part with the amount purported to be the refund without any additional payment.

Warm Regards,

Rajiv Pathak
